org.stringmatching.utils

Class IOUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.stringmatching.utils.IOUtils

  • public final class IOUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    A static utility package containing some useful methods for reading and writing bytes using InputStreams, OutputStreams, and RandomAccessFiles.
    Author:
    Matt Palmer

      • readEntireFile

        public static byte[] readEntireFile(java.io.File file)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Reads the bytes in a file into a single byte array and returns it.
        Parameters:
        file - The file to read.
        Returns:
        A byte array containing the file contents, of the same size as the file.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If the file size is greater than INTEGER.MAX_VALUE, which is the largest byte array that can be created. Also if the number of bytes read from the file does not match the size of the file, or if any other IOException occurs during opening or reading the file.

      • readEntireStream

        public static byte[] readEntireStream(java.io.InputStream input)
                               throws java.io.IOException
        Reads an input stream and returns a single array of bytes containing the stream contents.

        The implementation builds a list of byte array buffers, then copies them into a single byte array. This will use a bit more than twice as much memory as the length of the stream.

        The input stream is not closed when finished reading - that remains the responsibility of the code which passes it in.

        Parameters:
        input - The input stream to read.
        Returns:
        A byte array containing the stream contents.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is any problem reading from the InputStream.
